Q: Alice, Bob, and Claire are playing a game. At the start of the game, they are each holding a ball: Alice has a yellow ball, Bob has a blue ball, and Claire has a pink ball.
As the game progresses, pairs of players trade balls. First, Claire and Alice swap balls. Then, Alice and Bob swap balls. Finally, Claire and Bob swap balls. At the end of the game, Bob has the
Options:
(A) yellow ball
(B) blue ball
(C) pink ball
A: (A)

Q: Alice, Bob, and Claire are playing a game. At the start of the game, they are each holding a ball: Alice has a white ball, Bob has a purple ball, and Claire has a pink ball.
As the game progresses, pairs of players trade balls. First, Bob and Alice swap balls. Then, Bob and Claire swap balls. Finally, Bob and Alice swap balls. At the end of the game, Alice has the
Options:
(A) white ball

(C) pink ball
A: (C)

Q: Alice, Bob, and Claire are dancers at a square dance. At the start of a song, they each have a partner: Alice is dancing with Lola, Bob is dancing with Rodrigo, and Claire is dancing with Patrick.
Throughout the song, the dancers often trade partners. First, Alice and Bob switch partners. Then, Claire and Bob switch partners. Finally, Bob and Alice switch partners. At the end of the dance, Alice is dancing with
Options:
(A) Lola
(B) Rodrigo
(C) Patrick
A: (C)

Q: In a game of musical chairs, five people - Alice, Bob, Claire, Dave, and Eve - take turns sitting in a chair. The game starts with Alice sitting in the chair, while the others stand around. Then, in each round, the person sitting in the chair stands up and the next person in line (counting around the table) takes their place. The game ends when the chair is empty.
If the game starts with Alice in the chair and the others in the following order: Bob, Claire, Dave, and Eve, then in the first round, the chair is left empty by Alice, and the next person in line, Bob, should take the chair. In the second round, the person sitting in the chair, Bob, stands up and the next person in line, Claire, should take the chair. In the third round, the person sitting in the chair, Claire, stands up and the next person in line, Dave, should take the chair. In the fourth round, the person sitting in the chair, Dave, stands up and the next person in line, Eve, should take the chair. In the fifth round, the person sitting in the chair, Eve, stands up and the next person in line, Alice, should take the chair. Finally, in the last round, the person sitting in the chair, Alice, stands up and the chair remains empty. The person who ends up sitting in the chair at the end of the game is
